5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68bb2e65f9db348adc0af2f1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Alyssa%20Powell%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ERoughly%20one%20in%2010%20pregnant%20women%20in%20the%20US%20undergoes%20a%20cesarean%20section%20that%20experts%20say%20could%20have%20been%20avoided.%20One%20of%20the%20strongest%20predictors%20of%20her%20risk%20of%20a%20medically%20unnecessary%20C-section%20isn't%20her%20age%2C%20health%2C%20or%20pregnancy%20complications%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20the%20C-section%20rate%20at%20the%20hospital%20where%20she%20delivers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20best%20ways%20to%20avert%20an%20unnecessary%20C-section%20is%20to%20choose%20a%20hospital%20with%20low%20rates%20for%20the%20procedure%2C%20experts%20say.%20Yet%20pregnant%20women%20looking%20for%20this%20data%20may%20come%20up%20short.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnly%2011%20states%20make%20hospital%20C-section%20rates%20easily%20accessible%20on%20public%20websites%2C%20Business%20Insider%20found.%20Most%20states%20either%20say%20hospital%20C-section%20rates%20are%20confidential%20or%20release%20data%20only%20in%20response%20to%20formal%20public%20records%20or%20data%20requests.%20Some%20hospitals%20voluntarily%20disclose%20their%20C-section%20rates%20in%20response%20to%20annual%20consumer%20surveys%3B%20many%20do%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F0VyD9%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Choropleth%20map%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F0VyD9%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20results%20is%20a%20patchwork%20of%20disclosures%20that%20can%20hide%20significant%20C-section%20rate%20swings%20across%20nearby%20hospitals.%20Business%20Insider%20requested%20C-section%20data%20from%20all%2050%20states%20and%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%20An%20analysis%20of%20the%20first%2021%20to%20produce%20data%20reveals%20some%20hospitals%20performed%20surgeries%20on%20fewer%20than%205%25%20of%20women%20with%20low-risk%20pregnancies%20%E2%80%94%20those%20who%20are%20least%20likely%20to%20require%20surgery%20to%20safely%20deliver%20their%20babies%20since%20they%20are%20pregnant%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20are%20at%20full%20term%2C%20are%20not%20delivering%20twins%2C%20and%20whose%20babies%20are%20head-down%20rather%20than%20breech.%20On%20the%20high%20end%2C%2010%20hospitals%20operated%20on%20around%2050%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaternal%20healthcare%20providers%2C%20academics%20who%20study%20C-section%20rates%20and%20maternal%20health%20outcomes%2C%20and%20consumer%20advocates%20say%20that%20states'%20decision%20not%20to%20publicly%20publish%20hospital%20C-section%20rates%20benefits%20some%20hospitals%20competing%20for%20patients%20%E2%80%94%20but%20deprives%20pregnant%20women%20of%20critical%20information%20about%20their%20healthcare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20a%20priority%20for%20them%2C%20and%20frankly%2C%20some%20hospitals%20are%20embarrassed%20by%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Eugene%20Declercq%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20community%20health%20sciences%20at%20Boston%20University%20who%20studies%20the%20impact%20of%20federal%20and%20state%20policy%20on%20maternal%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20hospitals%20just%20cut%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20Declercq%20said.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20should%20know%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228d7a710c-acfd-4c6a-b33b-083597ef92dd%5C%22%3EA%20far%20higher%20rate%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERachel%20Bruns%2C%20a%20communications%20specialist%20in%20Iowa%2C%20didn't%20know%20the%20C-section%20rate%20at%20the%20hospital%20she%20picked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBruns%2C%20then%2031%20years%20old%2C%20was%20healthy%20and%20pregnant%20for%20the%20first%20time%20with%20a%20full-term%20baby%20positioned%20face-down%20%E2%80%94%20an%20ideal%20candidate%20for%20a%20vaginal%20delivery%2C%20her%20medical%20records%20show.%20About%20a%20week%20past%20her%20due%20date%2C%20Bruns'%20doctor%20induced%20her%20labor%20with%20Pitocin%2C%20a%20medication%20that%20causes%20the%20uterus%20to%20contract.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENurses%20maxed%20out%20Bruns'%20Pitocin%20dosage%2C%20but%20she%20never%20dilated%20beyond%204%20centimeters%20and%20never%20began%20to%20push.%20Bruns%20remembers%20her%20doctor%20saying%20she%20was%20unlikely%20to%20deliver%20vaginally.%20Bruns'%20labor%20had%20%26quot%3Bfailed%20to%20progress%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20her%20medical%20records%2C%20and%20her%20doctor%20recommended%20a%20C-section.%20Bruns%2C%20who%20says%20she%20was%20exhausted%20and%20scared%2C%20consented.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20her%20operation%2C%20lying%20in%20the%20recovery%20room%20unable%20to%20hold%20her%20newborn%20daughter%20without%20pain%2C%20Bruns%20felt%20a%20lingering%2C%20corrosive%20doubt%3A%20Was%20her%20surgery%20actually%20necessary%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBruns'%20amniotic%20sac%20had%20not%20ruptured%2C%20so%20she%20remembered%20her%20doctor%20said%20she%20could%20have%20attempted%20a%20second%20induction.%20Her%20labor%20had%20been%20long%20%E2%80%94%2016.5%20hours%2C%20according%20to%20her%20medical%20paperwork%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20American%20College%20of%20Obstetricians%20and%20Gynecologists%20says%20that%20women%20who%20are%20induced%2C%20like%20Bruns%2C%20often%20have%20significantly%20longer%20labors%3B%20even%20when%20their%20amniotic%20sac%20is%20ruptured%2C%20which%20speeds%20up%20labor%2C%20it%20could%20safely%20take%20up%20to%2018%20hours%20to%20reach%20the%20active%20pushing%20stage.%20She%20and%20her%20baby%20were%20healthy%20and%20had%20tolerated%20labor%20well%2C%20the%20kind%20of%20patients%20for%20whom%2C%20even%20in%20a%20prolonged%20early%20labor%2C%20ACOG%20recommends%20a%20C-section%20%26quot%3Bshould%20be%20avoided.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBruns%20couldn't%20shake%20it.%20She%20later%20asked%20Iowa's%20Department%20of%20Public%20Health%20and%20Human%20Services%20for%20hospital%20C-section%20rates.%20The%20department%20initially%20said%20those%20were%20confidential%2C%20but%20eventually%20released%20them%20after%20a%20lengthy%20negotiation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20was%20stark.%20In%20the%20year%20Bruns%20delivered%20her%20daughter%20and%20in%20the%20four%20successive%20years%2C%20the%20hospital%20where%20she%20delivered%20had%20a%20C-section%20rate%2015%25%20higher%20than%20the%20state%20average%2C%20a%20finding%20Business%20Insider's%20own%20analysis%20of%20Iowa%20hospital%20delivery%20data%20confirmed.%20Over%20those%20same%20five%20years%2C%20doctors%20at%20her%20hospital%20performed%20surgeries%20on%20women%20with%20no%20prior%20C-sections%2C%20like%20Bruns%2C%20at%20nearly%20double%20the%20rate%20on%20average%20as%20the%20doctors%20at%20a%20hospital%20located%202%20miles%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20to%20make%20peace%20with%2C%26quot%3B%20Bruns%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20had%20known%2C%20I%20would%20have%20chosen%20a%20different%20hospital.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Iowa%20Department%20of%20Health%20and%20Human%20Services%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20medically%20necessary%2C%20a%20C-section%20is%20a%20lifesaving%20surgery.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjamanetwork.com%2Fjournals%2Fjama%2Ffullarticle%2F2473490%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20large%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20up%20to%2019%25%20of%20all%20deliveries%20should%20be%20C-sections%20to%20protect%20the%20health%20and%20lives%20of%20women%20and%20their%20babies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20C-section%20rate%20is%20far%20higher%20%E2%80%94%20over%2032%25.%20That%20suggests%20that%20around%20one%20in%20three%20C-sections%20could%20be%20avoided%2C%20eliminating%20nearly%20half%20a%20million%20surgeries%20each%20year%20that%20leave%20women%20at%20a%20higher%20risk%20of%20hemorrhages%2C%20blood%20clots%2C%20and%20infections%2C%20and%20more%20likely%20to%20develop%20dangerous%20complications%20in%20future%20pregnancies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndividual%20hospital%20C-section%20rates%20vary%20widely%2C%20ranging%20from%20extremes%20as%20low%20as%207%25%20and%20as%20high%20as%2070%25%2C%20a%20recent%20study%20of%20data%20from%2044%20states%20shows.%20A%20woman's%20age%2C%20health%2C%20whether%20she's%20obese%2C%20and%20pre-existing%20conditions%2C%20such%20as%20diabetes%20or%20a%20previous%20C-section%2C%20may%20increase%20the%20chance%20that%20her%20baby%20is%20most%20safely%20delivered%20by%20C-section.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMultiple%20studies%20document%20that%20the%20hospital%20a%20woman%20chooses%20remains%20one%20of%20her%20biggest%20risk%20factors%20for%20undergoing%20a%20medically%20unnecessary%20C-section%2C%20after%20controlling%20for%20age%2C%20health%2C%20race%2C%20hospital%20delivery%20volume%2C%20and%20a%20host%20of%20other%20variables.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22eb3fa7e5-ac7f-4d82-a02b-395e0e3d09a4%5C%22%3EThe%20delivery%20business%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20hospitals%20do%20more%20unnecessary%20Cesarean%20deliveries%20than%20other%20hospitals%2C%26quot%3B%20reads%20a%20website%20run%20in%20partnership%20with%20California's%20Department%20of%20Public%20Health%20that%20links%20to%20annual%20C-section%20rate%20data%20for%20each%20hospital%20in%20the%20state.%20To%20lower%20your%20risk%20of%20surgery%2C%20the%20site%20recommends%2C%20%26quot%3Bchoose%20a%20hospital%20with%20lower%20Cesarean%20delivery%20rates.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20transparency%20is%20rare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeven%20other%20states%20with%20a%20combined%2023%20million%20residents%20%E2%80%94%20Arizona%2C%20Arkansas%2C%20Colorado%2C%20Hawaii%2C%20Idaho%2C%20Nebraska%2C%20and%20South%20Dakota%20%E2%80%94%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20hospital%20cesarean%20delivery%20rate%20data%20is%20confidential%2C%20either%20by%20department%20policy%20or%20state%20law.%20The%20Louisiana%20Department%20of%20Health%20said%20the%20state%20does%20not%20track%20C-section%20rates%20by%20hospital%20%E2%80%94%20the%20only%20state%20in%20the%20country%20that%20claimed%20not%20to%20track%20this%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlaska%20initially%20cited%20confidentiality%2C%20but%20released%20the%20data%20after%20Business%20Insider%20requested%20more%20information%20about%20the%20department's%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Idaho%20Department%20of%20Health%20and%20Welfare%20spokesperson%20suggested%20that%20Business%20Insider%20ask%20the%20state's%20hospital%20association%2C%20a%20private%20trade%20group.%20The%20Idaho%20Hospital%20Association%20and%20the%20Idaho%20Medical%20Association%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20requests%20for%20comment.%20The%20hospital%20associations%20for%20the%20seven%20other%20states%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20request%2C%20declined%20to%20produce%20hospital%20C-section%20rate%20data%2C%20or%20said%20their%20organization%20does%20not%20track%20C-section%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20from%20the%20Hawaii%20State%20Department%20of%20Health%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20department%20has%20a%20%26quot%3Blong-standing%20policy%26quot%3B%20against%20publicly%20disclosing%20hospital%20C-section%20rates%2C%20saying%20comparisons%20would%20be%20unfair%20to%20hospitals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BC-section%20rates%20may%20vary%20significantly%20due%20to%20differences%20in%20patient%20populations%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Hawaii%20spokesperson%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3Bas%20well%20as%20differences%20in%20hospital%20practices%2C%20capacity%2C%20or%20available%20services.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDozens%20of%20other%20states%20and%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%2C%20do%20not%20readily%20publicly%20publish%20hospital%20C-section%20rates.%20Instead%2C%20they%20only%20release%20that%20information%20in%20response%20to%20public%20records%20or%20data%20requests%2C%20sometimes%20for%20a%20hefty%20fee.%20The%20Utah%20Department%20of%20Health%20and%20Human%20Services%2C%20for%20example%2C%20initially%20priced%20the%20data%20at%20%241%2C800%20when%20reached%20in%20mid-September.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20reached%20for%20comment%20in%20October%2C%20Josie%20Thacker%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20Utah%20Department%20of%20Health%20and%20Human%20Services%2C%20said%20that%20hospital%20C-section%20rates%20in%20Utah%20would%20eventually%20be%20available%20for%20free%20on%20a%20public%20website%2C%20which%20is%20undergoing%20an%20update.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUntil%20the%20update%20is%20complete%2C%20the%20fee%20for%20the%20data%20you%20requested%20is%20%24900%2C%26quot%3B%20Thacker%20wrote%20to%20Business%20Insider%20in%20an%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20keeping%20C-section%20rates%20out%20of%20the%20public%20eye%20%E2%80%94%20either%20by%20withholding%20data%20or%20not%20making%20it%20readily%20accessible%20%E2%80%94%20health%20departments%20put%20the%20interests%20of%20hospitals%20over%20pregnant%20women's%20rights%20to%20make%20informed%20choices%20about%20their%20medical%20care%2C%20experts%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHospitals%20traditionally%20operate%20labor%20and%20delivery%20departments%20at%20a%20financial%20loss%20unless%20patient%20volume%20and%20insurance%20reimbursements%20are%20kept%20high%2C%20according%20to%20former%20hospital%20administrators%20and%20recent%20industry%20analysis.%20Each%20patient%20%E2%80%94%20every%20woman%20in%20labor%20and%20baby%20delivered%20%E2%80%94%20is%20valuable%20to%20hospitals%20looking%20to%20turn%20a%20profit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20hospitals%20go%20to%20extremes.%20Two%20lawsuits%20in%20particular%2C%20while%20neither%20involves%20allegations%20of%20medically%20unnecessary%20C-sections%2C%20illustrate%20the%20lengths%20some%20hospitals%20allegedly%20go%20to%20capture%20a%20larger%20share%20of%20the%20delivery%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20Tenet%20Healthcare%20Corporation%2C%20which%20at%20the%20time%20operated%2079%20hospitals%2C%20paid%20over%20%24513%20million%20to%20settle%20federal%20and%20state%20charges%20accusing%20the%20hospital%20giant%20and%20its%20subsidiary%20hospitals%20in%20Georgia%20of%20engaging%20in%20an%20illegal%20kickback%20scheme%20to%20swell%20their%20delivery%20business.%20Tenet%20admitted%20responsibility%20and%20agreed%20to%20a%20court-appointed%20monitor%2C%20and%20two%20of%20its%20subsidiaries%20pleaded%20guilty%20to%20conspiracy%20to%20defraud%20the%20United%20States%20and%20violate%20the%20federal%20Anti-Kickback%20Statute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20same%20year%2C%20a%202016%20jury%20awarded%20%2416%20million%20in%20damages%20in%20a%20civil%20suit%20against%20Brookwood%20Medical%20Center%20in%20Birmingham%2C%20Alabama%2C%20a%20hospital%20that%20at%20the%20time%20was%20majority-owned%20by%20Tenet%2C%20in%20part%20for%20launching%20an%20aggressive%20marketing%20blitz%20on%20television%2C%20billboards%2C%20and%20social%20media%20advertising%20labor%20care%20philosophies%20and%20amenities%20that%20were%2C%20in%20reality%2C%20unavailable%20or%20directly%20conflicted%20with%20the%20hospital's%20own%20care%20policies%2C%20according%20to%20court%20filings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20jury%20found%20Brookwood%20was%20responsible%20for%20reckless%20fraud%20and%20medical%20negligence.%20Brookwood's%20current%20spokesperson%20referred%20Business%20Insider%20to%20Tenet%20for%20comment.%20Tenet%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20queries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222787adce-99b1-4063-9686-0e3f3dfb844d%5C%22%3EA%20patchwork%20of%20hospital%20disclosures%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20each%20pregnant%20woman's%20choice%20of%20where%20to%20deliver%20so%20hard%20fought%2C%20a%20hospital's%20low%20C-section%20rate%20may%20become%20an%20advertising%20advantage%3B%20a%20high%20rate%2C%20a%20weak%20spot.%20Relatively%20low%20C-section%20rates%20are%20used%20in%20promotional%20materials%20at%20large%20hospital%20systems%20like%20Kaiser%20Permanente%20or%20Sutter%20Health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20hospitals%20argue%20that%20C-section%20rate%20disclosure%20would%20bias%20consumers%20against%20facilities%20with%20higher%20C-section%20rates%2C%20said%20Dr.%20Emily%20White%20VanGompel%2C%20a%20family%20medicine%20doctor%20and%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Illinois%20Chicago%20who%20studies%20how%20organizations%20impact%20C-section%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20argument%20is%20simple%3A%20If%20potential%20patients%20can%20look%20up%20a%20hospital's%20delivery%20rate%20data%2C%20%26quot%3Bthey're%20going%20to%20just%20all%20go%20to%20see%20the%20hospital%20with%20the%20lowest%20C-section%20rates%2C%26quot%3B%20White%20VanGompel%20said%2C%20which%20could%20be%20unfair%20to%20hospitals%20that%20treat%20more%20women%20with%20complicated%20or%20high-risk%20pregnancies.%20That%20logic%20falls%20apart%20on%20closer%20scrutiny%2C%20she%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20since%20many%20hospitals%20that%20serve%20high-risk%20pregnant%20women%20still%20manage%20to%20keep%20their%20low-risk%20C-section%20rates%20low.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20better%20compare%20C-section%20rates%20at%20hospitals%20that%20treat%20different%20types%20of%20patients%2C%20maternal%20health%20experts%20recommend%20looking%20at%20the%20rate%20doctors%20operate%20on%20low-risk%20pregnancies.%20Women%20with%20low-risk%20pregnancies%20are%20the%20least%20likely%20to%20require%20surgery%20to%20safely%20deliver%20their%20babies%2C%20so%20this%20metric%20is%20one%20of%20the%20best%20to%20evaluate%20a%20hospital's%20possible%20cesarean%20overuse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20say%20a%20hospital's%20administration%20and%20delivery%20policies%20have%20an%20outsize%20influence%20on%20the%20number%20of%20C-sections%20it%20performs.%20Publicly%20disclosing%20hospitals'%20low-risk%20C-section%20rates%20not%20only%20benefits%20women%20as%20consumers%20but%20could%20also%20encourage%20hospitals%20to%20safely%20support%20more%20vaginal%20deliveries%2C%20said%20White%20VanGompel%2C%20Declercq%2C%20and%20four%20other%20public%20health%20and%20maternal%20health%20researchers%20at%20the%20schools%20of%20medicine%20at%20Stanford%20University%2C%20Johns%20Hopkins%20University%2C%20the%20University%20of%20Michigan%2C%20and%20Harvard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20California%2C%20hospitals%20participating%20in%20a%20state-led%20initiative%20to%20lower%20low-risk%20C-section%20rates%20publicly%20published%20their%20C-section%20rates%2C%20among%20other%20maternal%20healthcare%20improvement%20strategies.%20Over%20five%20years%2C%20the%20state's%20low-risk%20C-section%20rate%20declined%20from%2026%25%20to%2022.8%25%20%E2%80%94%20a%2012%25%20drop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20hospitals%20already%20voluntarily%20disclose%20their%20low-risk%20C-section%20rate%20through%20a%20maternal%20health%20survey%20conducted%20annually%20by%20The%20Leapfrog%20Group%2C%20a%20healthcare%20transparency%20and%20consumer%20advocacy%20organization%20that%20publishes%20the%20results%20in%20a%20searchable%20database.%20In%202024%2C%20over%201%2C700%20hospitals%20%E2%80%94%20around%2070%25%20of%20those%20surveyed%20%E2%80%94%20disclosed%20maternity%20care%20quality%20data%2C%20including%20C-section%20rates%2C%20according%20to%20the%20group's%202025%20maternal%20healthcare%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESignificant%20blind%20spots%20remain.%20Springhill%20Medical%20Center%2C%20the%20only%20for-profit%20hospital%20in%20Mobile%2C%20Alabama%2C%20for%20example%2C%20declined%20to%20respond%20to%20Leapfrog's%202025%20survey.%20Doctors%20at%20that%20hospital%20performed%20surgeries%20on%2037.5%25%20of%20women%20with%20low-risk%20pregnancies%20on%20average%20between%202018%20and%202024%20%E2%80%94%20among%20the%20highest%20average%20rates%20in%20the%20state%20over%20those%20same%20years%2C%20according%20to%20Alabama%20Department%20of%20Public%20Health%20data%20obtained%20by%20Business%20Insider%20after%20filing%20a%20data%20request.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20known%20if%20any%20of%20those%20C-sections%20could%20have%20been%20avoided%2C%20but%20the%20lack%20of%20publicly%20available%20data%20meant%20expectant%20mothers%20could%20not%20compare%20Springhill's%20rate%20to%20those%20of%20surrounding%20hospitals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpringhill's%20average%20low-risk%20C-section%20rate%20from%202018%20to%202024%20was%2033%25%20higher%20than%20at%20a%20nearby%20hospital%20with%20roughly%20the%20same%20number%20of%20low-risk%20deliveries%2C%20and%20nearly%2047%25%20higher%20than%20a%20university%20teaching%20hospital%20that%20specializes%20in%20women%20with%20higher-risk%20pregnancies.%20The%20three%20hospitals%20are%20located%20within%206%20miles%20of%20one%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSpringhill%20Medical%20Center%20remains%20committed%20to%20safe%2C%20evidence-based%20care%20for%20all%20patients%2C%26quot%3B%20Deanna%20Kyrimis%2C%20the%20president%20and%20CEO%20of%20Springhill%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWe%20rigorously%20monitor%20our%20clinical%20outcomes%20and%20engage%20in%20a%20comprehensive%20quality%20review%20process%20%E2%80%94%20including%20case-by-case%20evaluations%20of%20cesarean%20deliveries%20%E2%80%94%20to%20ensure%20they%20align%20with%20medical%20necessity%20and%20best%20practices%2C%20supporting%20the%20highest%20standard%20of%20care%20for%20mothers%20and%20babies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20identified%20similar%20patterns%20of%20hospitals%20declining%20to%20disclose%20to%20Leapfrog%20comparatively%20high%20C-section%20rates%20for%20low-risk%20pregnancies%20in%20Alaska%2C%20Maine%2C%20Maryland%2C%20Massachusetts%2C%20Mississippi%2C%20Nevada%2C%20Rhode%20Island%2C%20Vermont%2C%20Washington%2C%20and%20Wisconsin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Arkansas%2C%20where%20hospital%20C-section%20rates%20are%20confidential%2C%20more%20than%20a%20quarter%20of%20women%20with%20low-risk%20pregnancies%20deliver%20their%20babies%20by%20C-section%20%E2%80%94%20the%2010th%20highest%20rate%20in%20the%20US%2C%20according%20to%20federal%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20Arkansas%20hospitals%20surveyed%2C%2040%25%20declined%20to%20respond%20to%20Leapfrog's%20maternal%20health%20survey.%20None%20of%20those%20Arkansas%20hospitals%20contacted%20by%20Business%20Insider%20disclosed%20their%20low-risk%20C-section%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhospital-c-section-rates-state-data-map-2025-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1760083801000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68bb2e4532af4d666ef75d90%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhospital-c-section-rates-state-data-map-2025-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Experts%20say%20one%20way%20to%20avoid%20unnecessary%20C-sections%20is%20to%20choose%20a%20hospital%20with%20low%20rates%20for%20the%20procedure.%20But%20many%20states%20withhold%20that%20data.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hbeckler%40insider.com%20(Hannah%20Beckler)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhospital-c-section-rates-state-data-map-2025-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Cruise%20missiles%2C%20yacht%20rock%2C%20and%20hot%20girls%20for%20capitalism%3A%20A%20night%20at%20The%20Free%20Press'%20afterparty%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20collage%20of%20Bari%20Weiss%20and%20imagery%20of%20a%20party%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68e6cbe45dbc4fd10daa7b31%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ENoam%20Galai%2FStringer%2FGetty%3B%20Getty%20Images%3B%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E