22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68e8397acc993f9955cfee5b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22975%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESina%20Chehrazi%2C%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Nayya.%3Cp%3ENayya%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EGoogle%20struck%20a%20deal%20with%20AI%20startup%20Nayya%20to%20help%20employees%20better%20engage%20with%20their%20benefits.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Big%20Tech%20giant%20faced%20backlash%20after%20requiring%20its%20employees%20to%20share%20personal%20data%20with%20Nayya.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENayya%20said%20the%20requirement%20originated%20with%20Google.%20Google%20updated%20its%20policy%20after%20BI's%20reporting.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle's%20bet%20on%20an%20AI%20startup%20to%20streamline%20employee%20benefits%20quickly%20turned%20into%20a%20privacy%20firestorm%20on%20Wednesday.%20The%20company%20told%20staff%20they'd%20have%20to%20hand%20over%20personal%20data%20to%20healthcare%20startup%20Nayya%20to%20use%20their%20health%20benefits%20%E2%80%94%20a%20move%20that%20Nayya's%20CEO%20says%20is%20rare%20among%20its%20partners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle's%20initial%20data%20sharing%20requirements%20came%20from%20the%20Big%20Tech%20giant%2C%20not%20from%20the%20startup%2C%20Nayya's%20CEO%20Sina%20Chehrazi%20shared%20with%20Business%20Insider.%20Nearly%20every%20other%20business%20Nayya%20works%20with%20allows%20its%20employees%20to%20opt%20in%20to%20sharing%20different%20pieces%20of%20their%20personal%20data%20as%20they%20see%20fit%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20haven't%20really%20seen%20anything%20like%20this%20before.%20It's%20usually%2C%20go%20in%20and%20get%20as%20much%20help%20as%20you%20need%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFounded%20in%202020%2C%20New%20York-based%20Nayya%20has%20raised%20over%20%24130%20million%20for%20its%20software%20that%20helps%20employees%20navigate%20their%20healthcare%20and%20financial%20benefits.%20Its%20backers%20include%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhr-software-tech-companies-employees-productivity-workday-oracle-adp-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etop%20HR%20management%20tech%3C%2Fa%3E%20companies%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feveryone-hates-workday-human-resources-customer-service-software-fortune-500-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EWorkday%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20ADP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ai-health-tool-opt-in-risk-losing-benefits-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle%3C%2Fa%3E%20originally%20told%20US-based%20employees%20this%20month%20that%20they%20would%20need%20to%20give%20startup%20Nayya%20access%20to%20their%20personal%20data%20in%20order%20to%20access%20their%20health%20benefits%2C%20Business%20Insider%20reported%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20announcement%20drew%20criticism%20from%20employees%20who%20worried%20about%20being%20forced%20to%20share%20private%20health%20data%20with%20a%20third-party%20company.%20Google's%20initial%20guidance%20suggested%20that%20workers%20who%20declined%20wouldn't%20be%20eligible%20for%20any%20health%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-ai-health-tool-opt-in-risk-losing-benefits-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle%20updated%20its%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20BI's%20Wednesday%20story%20to%20state%20that%20employees%20can%20elect%20not%20to%20share%20their%20data%20with%20Nayya%20without%20their%20benefits%20enrollment%20being%20affected.%20The%20company%20told%20BI%20for%20this%20story%20that%20employees%20can%20simply%20not%20opt%20in%20to%20using%20Nayya%20if%20they%20don't%20want%20to%20share%20their%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20AI%20tools%20like%20OpenAI's%20ChatGPT%20spread%20like%20wildfire%2C%20employees%20are%20increasingly%20sharing%20sensitive%20company%20information%20with%20the%20tech%2C%20often%20without%20realizing%20it.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20employers%2C%20including%20Big%20Tech%20companies%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-tracks-employees-ai-use-creates-game-to-boost-adoption-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMeta%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-internal-memo-using-ai-no-longer-optional-github-copilot-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-employees-use-ai-or-get-left-behind-gemini-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20are%20pushing%20employees%20to%20use%20AI%20in%20their%20day-to-day%20work%20%E2%80%94%20but%20sometimes%20mandating%20their%20usage%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20expanded%20data%20collection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20future%20of%20data%20is%20consent.%20We%20are%20only%20interested%20in%20helping%20the%20people%20who%20want%20the%20help%2C%20and%20only%20in%20the%20way%20that%20they'd%20like%20to%20get%20that%20help%2C%26quot%3B%20Chehrazi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fde8428a-8a01-4ebf-9cf4-427ba41f67a8%5C%22%3EThe%20AI-powered%20health%20benefits%20play%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETech%20has%20been%20trying%20to%20provide%20better%20employee%20benefits%20navigation%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENayya%2C%20like%20a%20number%20of%20its%20competitors%2C%20is%20now%20using%20AI%20to%20tailor%20benefits%20recommendations.%20Employees%20can%20give%20Nayya%20information%20about%20their%20health%20and%20lifestyle%2C%20and%20the%20startup%20will%20use%20that%20data%20to%20guide%20those%20employees%20to%20benefits%20they%20already%20have.%20The%20tech%20also%20keeps%20track%20of%20employees'%20existing%20benefits%20usage%2C%20like%20how%20much%20of%20their%20deductible%20has%20been%20met.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENayya%20says%20it%20currently%20provides%20benefits%20navigation%20tech%20to%20over%201%2C000%20employers%2C%20from%20law%20firm%20Goodwin%20Procter%20to%20health%20system%20Bon%20Secours%20Mercy%20Health.%20Most%20of%20Nayya's%20contracts%20are%20with%20employers'%20systems%20of%20record%2C%20the%20benefits%20management%20software%20they%20already%20use%2C%20like%20Workday%20or%20ADP%2C%20Chehrazi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENayya%20also%20contracts%20directly%20with%20some%20employers.%20While%20Google%20uses%20Workday%20to%20manage%20administrative%20tasks%20like%20payroll%2C%20it%20uses%20a%20different%20platform%20to%20manage%20its%20employee%20benefits%20called%20Benefitfocus%2C%20Chehrazi%20said.%20To%20connect%20to%20Benefitfocus%2C%20Nayya%20contracts%20directly%20with%20Google.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20struck%20a%20direct%20contract%20this%20year%20with%20Nayya%20to%20help%20employees%20decide%20which%20benefits%20they%20should%20opt%20into%20during%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopen-enrollment-healthcare-companies-demystify-insurance-process-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eopen%20enrollment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Nayya%20CEO%20Sina%20Chehrazi%20told%20BI.%20That%20integration%20leverages%20Nayya's%20benefits%20decision%20support%20platform%20rather%20than%20the%20startup's%20agentic%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20of%20Nayya's%20tools%20will%20be%20rolled%20out%20to%20Google%20employees%20in%20future%20months%2C%20Chehrazi%20said%2C%20such%20as%20technology%20that%20helps%20employees%20save%20money%20by%20pre-filling%20and%20submitting%20reimbursement%20forms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENayya%20says%20it%20helps%20employees%20save%20money%2C%20including%20by%20leading%20them%20to%20fully-covered%20health%20services%20to%20avoid%20surprise%20bills.%20The%20return-on-investment%20for%20employers%20is%20less%20direct.%20In%20theory%2C%20employees%20who%20can%20take%20better%20advantage%20of%20their%20health%20benefits%20will%20be%20healthier%20on%20average%2C%20creating%20fewer%20large%20costs%20for%20their%20employers.%20Chehrazi%20said%20in%20the%20longer%20term%2C%20Nayya%20can%20show%